Today I noticed from writing a small test app (tracking down another bug) that the KeepAlive setting in the HttpWebRequest class does not have an effect in actually reusing the connection for further requests.

To prove this I have written a small test application which uses a WebClient to send requests to a given target url, you can see that the reuse option in the .NetFramework has an impact on the requests per second throughput (in my testcase with the test server it was factor 5).
So my guess is, that the connection is sending the correct header (since this was fixed by another Issue)
